				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Dumb Bard<a name="56977"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 16 04 4:41 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I was playing my bard in BOT the other day. We were in a group and pulled Oreen (or some such name). He wiped us because of a LD. We reassembled to go at him again. After we cleared the trash we were ready for a second go at him.
<br />

<br />
At some point I got it into my head that I should have invulnerability song up. I figured that it is never a bad thing to be invulnerable... Also I had had this song for about 10 levels and never found a use for it.
<br />

<br />
Well we had Oreen down to 20 percent and I figured I would try my song out.... I hit the invulnerability and sure enough we all got a message saying we were invulnerable to his attacks.. unfortunately, I discovered the hard way that we could not attack him either, the cleric could not heal anyone, and taunt was not working. Oreen lost interest in our tank and started whacking on our cleric. Needless to say the song wore off and the cleric went down, then everyone else went down. I could have hit invis and ran out but I figured I should take my lumps and let him kill me.
<br />

<br />
Boy was my group ticked off. I fessed up to my error and apologised profusely. I figure it should probably be a while before I go back to BOT.. my name is probably mud.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
